{{Object Class|utility=4|risk=5|properties=Entity Manifestation, Creating [[Phenomenon 99|temporary spaces]], Object Destruction, Object Creation}}

{{SimpleHeader|header=DESCRIPTION|background=rgba(75, 75, 75, 0.3)}}<!--hello source user. i hate descriptions so muhc it was a pain to think all this up-->
Object 22, also referred to as a 'cross', is a medium-sized device with three pronged legs. It has a tall, black body surrounded by dark steel plates. Nestled between these plates are small orange cylinders, acting as the fuel storage<ref>These hold small, aluminum balls capable of generating electromagnetic energy on their own.</ref>.  The Cross has shown the ability to manifest entities and destroy objects. {{Blurimage|file=Object22Alt2.png|caption=Iteration 2.}} It is believed that the Cross manifested anomalous abilities after continued use. The Cross also opens "rifts"<ref>These are theorised to form at an atomic level, explaining the destructive capabilities.</ref>, holes in levels that lead to [[The Void]]. It can be noted that multiple test participants have shown biological changes, specifically to the genome. Increased protein production is often a side effect of interacting with the device<ref>It is unknown as to why this happens</ref>. The device is now more valuable than all of the combined assets and incomes of Bilbury, England.

The first iteration of the device was created by the [[M.E.G.]], before being seized by the [[Party Crashers]]. The second iteration was handheld and tested in the Ieptus Testing Institute<ref>Location classified</ref>; It was then transported to the Starclip Testing Institute to be repaired after the device was damaged. The third and final iteration of the device was developed in the Frestway Testing Institute, remaining operational until [[Phenomenon 12|The Flicker]]. The Flicker causes the core to collapse, destroying itself.
Standing in front of the operational end of the device during activation is ill-advised, with internal bleeding and death almost guaranteed. Symptoms include:

* Strokes
* Seizures
* Internal bleeding
* Haemorrhage
* Cancer

A notable side effect of being hit with the device is teleportation, with some subjects being transported to [[The Void]] or [[The Broken]]<ref>There have been cases of partial teleportation, with subjects being split in half or losing appendages.</ref>.

The Cross has also shown the ability to "generate" objects, most notably [[Object 200]] from [[Phenomenon 99|Level 9.9]]. 9.9 was a notable temporary space, one of the first that remained stable for longer than a couple of seconds. During the generation of this space, numerous anonymous accounts bombarded [[Phenomenon 2|BACK-NET]] with website-creation requests, spreading information about the level. It is unknown who the creators were and how they got this information. This information was often incorrect and had mistakes. 
<!--bad first level mention!!-->
{{Collapse|final='''Close'''|initial='''Open Extracts'''|body=

''"Level 9.9 is a infinitely repeating street of houses. These houses can change shape, size, and material, but are always in the same position. Level  is eternally dark, due to The Veil. There is a small amount of light emitted by the stars, and the blood-ridden moon."'' - backnet049682://corpsewalker.net

''"Despite the fact that the level is seemingly infinite, there is an end. If you survive The Infinity Effect for long enough, you are guaranteed to reach a Train Station. A single train travels there, the Veil Metro. Upon stepping into the train, the Infinity Effect ceases, reversing all aftereffects. After a few seconds, the train will depart. After 5 hours, and 12 minutes- the train will stop. As soon as you step outside, you will be met with a dark; endless void."'' - backnet049682://dailymailrealorg.net

''"The Veil is the extra-dimensional plane separating [[The Void]] from Level 9.9. The Veil acts as a protective shields against entities that attempt to no-clip into the level, keeping them out of the main level. The main inhabitants of The Veil are Dunkelburrs. The only known entities able to pass through The Veil are Wanderers, making the level primarily inhabited by humans. '''Veil Ink''', also know as '''God Blood''' is the material that makes up the Veil, and transforms Vessels into Dunkelburrs. Veil Ink is corrosive, due to it being a mix of Sodium Hydroxide (15.24%), Bromine (21.53%), and [[Object 12]] (63.23%). '''Veil Rain''', also known as '''Angel Rain''' only occurs every ~9 hours, being caused by a mass-buildup of Veil Ink in The Veil, this buildup reaches a breaking point, eventually falling as a rain. This creates a major environmental hazard, it is advised to find cover as soon as it begins, due to Veil Ink's corrosive nature."'' - backnet956965://quakifinacorpalisation.org
|num=1}}
