{{SimpleHeader|header=USAGE|background=rgba(75, 75, 75, 0.3)}}
The Cross was designed in an effort to "force" a [[Phenomenon 99|temporary space]] to open. It generates unstable geometry before firing a small aluminium pellet into the wall, effectively forcing a no-clip. While in the Void, the vessel<ref>The Vessel is a small, titanium pellet.</ref> utilises small thrusters to move around, avoiding stable areas. This forces a [[Phenomenon 99|temporary space]] to open. A notable space is Level 9.9. It was similar in appearance to [[Level 9]], and existed for just 7 days<ref>The existence of these forced spaces has been discovered to be interlinked with the constant e, as the time measured out to e*e days.</ref>.
<references />
{{SimpleHeader|header=STARCLIP|background=rgba(75, 75, 75, 0.3)}}
The Starclip Incident occurred on the 25th of December, 2010. JC<ref>Operative James Carter</ref> walks into the Starclip Research Institute<ref>Location classified.</ref>, towards the experimental weaponry branch. Numerous tests of the Cross<ref>nicknamed the Catalyst at the time.</ref> were planned that day. JC enters the building, heading for the infirmary after falling down a flight of stairs. JC exits the infirmary at 14:53. JC immediately heads for Building B, entering at 14:56. Multiple devices are around, being tested live. JC puts on a yellow jumpsuit, preparing for the first test. JC enters a small section of Building B, the device sitting in the middle of the room. JC picks up a set of crucible tongs, using them to pick up the Core<ref>The Core is kept stored in a small locker to the left of the device.</ref>. 

JC places the Core into the device, accidentally offsetting one of the metal plates. The Core begins powering up, going critical 2.3 minutes later. The remaining pieces of the device are destroyed, the core is generating a gravitational force similar to that of a small asteroid. JC exits floor 1, unaware of the core's criticality. 

JC is found deceased on the second floor, blood pouring from his nose. The entirety of the experimental weaponry branch is evacuated, leaving only 15 casualties. The experimental weaponry branch is abandoned, alongside the entirety of the Starclip Institute<ref>Entry into the site is forbidden; attempting to do so will result in prosecution.</ref>.
