{{User:SmallaB/darkLogin|1=
The Cross was created by the [[M.E.G.]] for creating [[Phenomenon 99|temporary spaces]]<ref>designed by M.E.G operative James Carter.</ref>. The body consists of multiple steel plates surrounding a "core". This core generates energy in the barrel, before launching the vessel at high speeds<ref>The vessel is launched at around Mach 15.</ref>. The device was designed with storage and manoeuvrability in mind, small enough to fit in the trunk of a car, measuring at about 1.54m x 0.6m in dimension. 
{{Blurimage|file=Object22Alt.webp|caption=A theorised design, for iteration 1.}}
The front-end of the device consists of a barrel, roll and a firing pin. The barrel is the main barrel, measuring around 0.6m in length. The barrel is kept retracted within the body. The barrel has a small hatch at the end, stopping the vessel from falling out. The roll is a large, spinning cylinder built around the barrel. The roll generates electromagnetic force, powering the Core. The firing pin is a cylinder of small size, protruding from the top of the barrel. Pulling this pin releases the energy within the Core, launching the vessel out of the barrel.

The body consists of multiple steel plates surrounding the Core. The Core is a titanium ball of small proportion; the roll generates electromagnetic energy within it. The Core is made up of multiple aluminium rings, with a small sphere of titanium sitting in the middle. Around 100 milligrams of francium dust is placed within the sphere. Electromagnetic fields are generated within the core by the roll, decaying the francium into radium-223.
